  "title": "British Steel puts up to 2,700 jobs at risk",
  "text": "Up to 2,700 jobs at risk at British Steel\nCharlotte Edwards\nBusiness reporter, BBC News\nBritish Steel is launching a consultation that could see the closure of its two blast furnaces at Scunthorpe, affecting between 2,000 and 2,700 jobs.\nThe company's owner, Jingye, said the blast furnaces were \"no longer financially sustainable\" due to tough market conditions, the imposition of tariffs and higher environmental costs.\nBritish Steel chief executive Zengwei An said it was \"a necessary decision given the hugely challenging circumstances the business faces\".\nThe GMB union called it \"devastating news for the people of Scunthorpe\" and called on the government to do \"everything possible\" to secure the future of steelmaking at the site.",
